                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/0957: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-17T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 17, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1103. Department’s no. 1085, November 14, 6 p.m. and no. 1086, November 14, 7
                    p.m. Metals Reserve is quite willing that the tin to be transported for Russia
                    should precede that purchased for account of the Metals Reserve Company.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
